WEBVTT

00:04.771 --> 00:05.739 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Good evening.

00:05.772 --> 00:07.440 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
I'm Judy Woodruff.

00:07.474 --> 00:12.312 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
On the "NewsHour" tonight: After
16 years
of U.S. military presence and
sacrifice in

00:12.345 --> 00:18.451 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Afghanistan, and yesterday's
historic bomb
drop, where does that country
stand?

00:18.485 --> 00:24.991 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Then: As Easter approaches, we
go to Seville,
Spain, where the decline of
cloistered life

00:25.025 --> 00:28.294 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
is on full display in the city's
crumbling
convents.

00:28.328 --> 00:33.600 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: Convents like
Santa Ines here
in Seville are hidden treasures
from an earlier

00:33.633 --> 00:39.773 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
era, once small, but bustling
communities
now with fewer inhabitants and
walls that

00:39.806 --> 00:40.774 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
are decaying.

00:40.807 --> 00:42.575 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: And it's Friday.

00:42.609 --> 00:46.913 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Mark Shields and David Brooks
are here to
analyze the week's news.

00:46.946 --> 00:53.787 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
All that and more on tonight's
"PBS NewsHour."

00:53.820 --> 00:56.623 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
(BREAK)

00:56.656 --> 01:05.999 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: North Korea
issued a new warning
today to the United States.

01:06.032 --> 01:10.937 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
It came amid signs the North
might be getting
ready for another nuclear test.

01:10.970 --> 01:15.341 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The vice foreign minister
charged that the
Trump administration is -- quote
-- "more

01:15.375 --> 01:18.778 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
vicious and more aggressive"
than President
Obama's.

01:18.812 --> 01:24.350 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
HAN SONG RYOL, North Korean Vice
Foreign Minister
(through translator): We are
taking into account

01:24.384 --> 01:28.288 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
the most aggressive and
dangerous option that
the U.S. might come up with, and
we have also

01:28.321 --> 01:32.425 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
got our options, our
countermeasures ready
in our hands, which means we
will go to war

01:32.459 --> 01:34.194 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
if they choose.

01:34.227 --> 01:37.931 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: There's rising
speculation
that Pyongyang could carry out a
nuclear or

01:37.964 --> 01:40.300 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
a missile test tomorrow.

01:40.333 --> 01:46.039 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
That's when the North marks the
105th anniversary
of the birth of Kim Il-Sung, who
founded the

01:46.072 --> 01:49.142 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
hard-line communist state in
1948.

01:49.175 --> 01:54.747 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Russia, Syria and Iran say they
have sent
a -- quote -- "strong message"
to the U.S.

01:54.781 --> 01:57.083 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
not to attack Syria again.

01:57.117 --> 01:59.486 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Their foreign ministers met in
Moscow today.

01:59.519 --> 02:04.958 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
They warned that another U.S.
military strike
could have grave consequences
for regional

02:04.991 --> 02:07.026 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
and global security.

02:07.060 --> 02:12.398 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
President Trump ordered a cruise
missile barrage
in Syria last week, after
accusing its government

02:12.432 --> 02:14.767 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
of a poison gas attack.

02:14.801 --> 02:19.806 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
In Turkey, voters headed toward
a momentous
decision: whether to approve
greatly expanded

02:19.839 --> 02:23.409 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
powers for President Recep
Tayyip Erdogan.

02:23.443 --> 02:29.282 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Sunday's referendum has sharply
divided the
country, and European election
observers say

02:29.315 --> 02:32.585 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
the government has tried to
intimidate the
opposition.

02:32.619 --> 02:35.121 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Erdogan lashed out at them
today.

02:35.155 --> 02:40.793 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
RECEP TAYYIP ERDOGAN, Turkish
President (through
translator): Now they say, if
the result is

02:40.827 --> 02:43.496 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
yes, that means there are a lot
of problems.

02:43.530 --> 02:44.697 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
Who are you?

02:44.731 --> 02:46.666 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
First of all, you should know
your place.

02:46.699 --> 02:48.067 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
This is not your duty.

02:48.101 --> 02:51.471 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
You can't talk about what will
happen if the
result is yes or no.

02:51.504 --> 02:57.644 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Erdogan has
carried out a sweeping
crackdown since an attempted
coup last year.

02:57.677 --> 03:02.282 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Back in this country, death
penalty opponents
rallied in Little Rock,
Arkansas, against

03:02.315 --> 03:06.986 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
plans to execute seven death row
inmates by
the end of the month.

03:07.020 --> 03:10.890 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The protest featured celebrity
speakers and
hundreds of others.

03:10.924 --> 03:14.227 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The first execution is scheduled
for Monday
night.

03:14.260 --> 03:19.632 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Arkansas has not put anyone to
death since
2005, but officials say the
state's supply

03:19.666 --> 03:25.038 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
of a lethal injection drug is
about to pass
its expiration date.

03:25.071 --> 03:29.943 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
A federal judge in San Francisco
is being
asked to block President Trump's
executive

03:29.976 --> 03:32.812 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
order on so-called sanctuary
cities.

03:32.845 --> 03:38.084 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
It withholds federal funding
from cities that
won't cooperate on deporting
undocumented

03:38.117 --> 03:39.886 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
immigrants.

03:39.919 --> 03:45.558 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
San Francisco and Santa Clara
counties argued
today for a nationwide
injunction against

03:45.592 --> 03:48.328 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
enforcing the funding ban.

03:48.361 --> 03:52.932 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The Trump White House says that
it will not
release logs of its visitors.

03:52.966 --> 03:57.470 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Today's announcement was a break
from President
Obama's practice, but Trump
administration

03:57.503 --> 04:01.341 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
officials say that it is in line
with what
previous presidents did.

04:01.374 --> 04:06.145 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
They cited privacy and national
security concerns.

04:06.179 --> 04:10.850 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And Christians around the world
marked this
Good Friday with solemn
observances.

04:10.883 --> 04:16.756 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Pope Francis presided at the
traditional Way
of the Cross procession in Rome,
with thousands

04:16.789 --> 04:18.591 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
in attendance.

04:18.625 --> 04:22.895 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And in this country, hundreds of
people walked
the Brooklyn Bridge in New York
behind a man

04:22.929 --> 04:25.298 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
carrying a cross.

04:25.331 --> 04:31.371 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Still to come on the "NewsHour":
what a massive
bombing says about the U.S. role
in Afghanistan;

04:31.404 --> 04:38.311 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
decades of sexual abuse
uncovered at a prestigious
private boarding school;
preserving convents

04:38.344 --> 04:50.256 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
in Southern Spain; and much
more.

04:50.290 --> 04:57.630 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The United States' involvement
in Afghanistan
was brought into stark relief
yesterday with

04:57.664 --> 05:00.867 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
a massive airstrike in the
country's east.

05:00.900 --> 05:06.639 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
After nearly 16 years, thousands
of casualties
and billions of dollars, where
does the American

05:06.673 --> 05:07.974 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
effort stand?

05:08.007 --> 05:11.377 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And is the country any closer to
being stabilized?

05:11.411 --> 05:13.179 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
William Brangham begins our
coverage.

05:13.212 --> 05:18.618 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: The video
shows a remote
mountain valley suddenly
consumed by a blast

05:18.651 --> 05:21.754 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
equal to 11 tons of TNT.

05:21.788 --> 05:26.326 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The weapon, called a Massive
Ordnance Air
Burst, or MOAB, was used for the
first time

05:26.359 --> 05:29.762 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
on the battlefield yesterday in
this strike
against Islamic State forces.

05:29.796 --> 05:31.764 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
GEN.

05:31.798 --> 05:33.633 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JOHN NICHOLSON, Commander U.S.
Forces, Afghanistan:
This was the right weapon
against this target.

05:33.666 --> 05:37.570 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: In Kabul
today, the top
American commander in
Afghanistan, Army General

05:37.603 --> 05:42.709 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
John Nicholson, called its use a
tactical
decision, not a strategic change
in policy.

05:42.742 --> 05:44.510 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
GEN.

05:44.544 --> 05:48.448 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JOHN NICHOLSON: The enemy had
created bunkers,
tunnels and extensive mine
fields, and this

05:48.481 --> 05:53.586 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
weapon was used to reduce those
obstacles,
so we can continue our
offensive.

05:53.619 --> 05:57.490 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: The target
area was a district
in Nangarhar province, where
last weekend

05:57.523 --> 06:00.059 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
a U.S. special forces soldier
was killed.

06:00.093 --> 06:06.099 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
It, along with neighboring Logar
and Kunar
provinces, are rife with Islamic
State activity.

06:06.132 --> 06:11.204 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
At the same time, the Taliban
also continues
to control and contest broad
swathes of the

06:11.237 --> 06:13.139 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
Afghan countryside.

06:13.172 --> 06:17.810 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The Taliban and ISIS have
claimed responsibility
for a series of recent attacks
in Kabul that

06:17.844 --> 06:20.113 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
have shaken the capital.

06:20.146 --> 06:25.918 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Afghan officials say Thursday's
blast killed
36 Islamic State militants, but
no civilians.

06:25.952 --> 06:28.621 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
ISIS denied anyone was killed.

06:28.654 --> 06:33.426 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Afghan citizens appeared divided
on using
the bomb against ISIS, or
Da'esh, as it's

06:33.459 --> 06:35.194 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
also known.

06:35.228 --> 06:37.864 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MAN (through translator): We are
very happy,
and these kinds of bombs should
be used in

06:37.897 --> 06:40.767 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
future as well, so ISIS is
rooted out from
here.

06:40.800 --> 06:44.904 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MOHAMMED AMAN, Kabul Resident
(through translator):
Da'esh is the enemy of
Afghanistan.

06:44.937 --> 06:48.508 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But there are children there,
and they had
casualties from this bombing.

06:48.541 --> 06:50.376 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
The whole world condemns this
action.

06:50.410 --> 06:55.648 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: The U.S. still
has nearly
9,000 troops in Afghanistan, and
General Nicholson

06:55.681 --> 07:00.953 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
has said the NATO force there
needs a few
thousand more troops to train
and advise Afghan

07:00.987 --> 07:02.755 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
forces.

07:02.789 --> 07:07.260 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
It's those local forces who
continue to take
major casualties in the fight
against the

07:07.293 --> 07:09.195 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
insurgents.

07:09.228 --> 07:12.765 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
That ongoing fight will surely
be on the agenda
when President Trump's national
security adviser,

07:12.799 --> 07:15.935 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
H.R. McMaster, visits Kabul in
the weeks ahead.

07:15.968 --> 07:18.104 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
For the "PBS NewsHour," I'm
William Brangham.

07:18.137 --> 07:21.707 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: For more on all
of this, we
turn to Pamela Constable.

07:21.741 --> 07:26.512 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
She's the Washington Post bureau
chief in
Kabul and Islamabad.

07:26.546 --> 07:29.949 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
We're watching -- catching her,
that is, on
one of her trips home.

07:29.982 --> 07:33.953 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Pam, we're glad that you're here
to talk about
the developments of the last few
days, but

07:33.986 --> 07:36.856 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
also to take a look at the
bigger picture
in Afghanistan.

07:36.889 --> 07:40.159 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
First of all, Kabul, capital
city, how stable
is it?

07:40.193 --> 07:41.694 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
What does it feel like?

07:41.727 --> 07:43.129 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
PAMELA CONSTABLE, The Washington
Post: Well,
you know, it's a contradiction.

07:43.162 --> 07:44.931 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
It's a very busy, active city.

07:44.964 --> 07:47.433 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
If you walked around it in the
middle of the
day, you would think you were in
the middle

07:47.467 --> 07:52.438 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
of any other big, poor, but busy
city.

07:52.472 --> 07:56.576 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But there's a great feeling of
uncertainty
and tension at this time.

07:56.609 --> 08:01.881 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
There's been a series of very
bad suicide
bombings, most recently the one
at the military

08:01.914 --> 08:07.753 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
hospital last month, which was
extremely shocking,
I think, to Kabul residents, who
had gotten

08:07.787 --> 08:10.790 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
used to a certain sense of
stability and security.

08:10.823 --> 08:13.359 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And I think a lot of that is
gone now.

08:13.392 --> 08:19.332 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
It's also a city that really
shows the difficulties
Afghanistan's having
economically.

08:19.365 --> 08:24.770 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The streets are full of beggars,
full of drug
addicts, full of people who are
really struggling

08:24.804 --> 08:27.507 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
and looking for jobs, so it's a
bit of a sad
picture.

08:27.540 --> 08:29.642 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: What do you
attribute it to?

08:29.675 --> 08:31.944 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
PAMELA CONSTABLE: Oh, that's a
big question.

08:31.978 --> 08:33.279 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: It's a big
question.

08:33.312 --> 08:34.780 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
PAMELA CONSTABLE: Many things.

08:34.814 --> 08:37.450 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
I think first and foremost has
to be security.

08:37.483 --> 08:43.356 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I mean, you have got a very
persistent, very
sophisticated Taliban
insurgency, which is

08:43.389 --> 08:48.694 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
really doing lots and lots of
attacks across
the country, as well in the
capital.

08:48.728 --> 08:50.363 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: And getting
stronger.

08:50.396 --> 08:56.802 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
PAMELA CONSTABLE: Well,
certainly holding
its own, certainly able to carry
out very

08:56.836 --> 09:02.174 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
frightening and persistent
attacks, certainly
not close to winning, but
they're certainly

09:02.208 --> 09:04.010 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
doing pretty well.

09:04.043 --> 09:07.613 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Then you have ISIS, which is
known there as
Da'esh, which is a whole other
can of worms,

09:07.647 --> 09:13.519 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
as they say, a very different
sort of enemy,
more ruthless, less interested
in winning

09:13.553 --> 09:20.426 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
hearts and minds, more
foreign-based, more
extreme compared to the Taliban,
and, obviously,

09:20.459 --> 09:22.228 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
of greater concern to the
neighbors.

09:22.261 --> 09:26.098 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Russia, for example, is very
concerned about
ISIS, and less so about the
Taliban, which

09:26.132 --> 09:29.035 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
they appear to be reaching out
to in many
ways.

09:29.068 --> 09:31.270 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
So, that's number one.

09:31.304 --> 09:33.205 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And then following that is a
long list.

09:33.239 --> 09:40.646 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
There's corruption, there's
poverty, there
is tribal and regional problems,
and there's

09:40.680 --> 09:43.382 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
the persistent divisions within
the government
itself.

09:43.416 --> 09:50.222 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
So, people are quite frustrated,
and I think
very disillusioned by the lack
of progress

09:50.256 --> 09:51.490 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
on a lot of fronts.

09:51.524 --> 09:54.327 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Where do -- many
people place
the blame there.

09:54.360 --> 09:58.497 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I mean, do they blame the U.S.
for not keeping
more troops on the ground?

09:58.531 --> 10:01.100 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
Do they blame the Afghan
government?

10:01.133 --> 10:04.837 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
PAMELA CONSTABLE: I mean,
there's a tendency
to always blame the guy in
charge.

10:04.870 --> 10:07.006 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And, of course, that's President
Ghani.

10:07.039 --> 10:08.608 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And he deserves some of the
blame.

10:08.641 --> 10:10.610 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I think he probably took on more
than he could
chew.

