contains graphic
material and is not suitable
reading for children.

20:22.154 --> 20:25.324 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
That's a pretty telling thing to
put on a
report.

20:25.357 --> 20:26.325 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
PAUL MONES: Right.

20:26.358 --> 20:28.627 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And I read that and I thought,
really?

20:28.660 --> 20:31.263 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
You know, it was good enough to
sweep under
the rug.

20:31.296 --> 20:34.967 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And I understand that, but I
thought -- I
was turned of by that.

20:35.000 --> 20:39.905 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I thought that, yes, it was that
graphic,
but now they're saying you have
to have -- you

20:39.938 --> 20:41.707 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
know, keep it away from unwanted
eyes.

20:41.740 --> 20:48.080 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I viewed this as being a -- the
only reason,
as I said -- I will have to
reiterate this

20:48.113 --> 20:55.687 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
-- if The Globe didn't come
knocking, if there
wasn't a rising march of voices
of students

20:55.721 --> 21:02.628 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
from private schools yelling for
relief, Horace
Mann School, St. George's School
around the

21:02.661 --> 21:05.230 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
country, they would have done
nothing at all.

21:05.264 --> 21:07.532 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: All right,
gentlemen, we
will see you on TV tonight.

21:07.566 --> 21:08.533 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
Thank you very much.

21:08.567 --> 21:09.968 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
PAUL MONES: OK.

21:10.002 --> 21:13.171 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
Thanks a lot.

21:13.205 --> 21:19.244 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
JONATHAN SALTZMAN: Thanks, Hari.

21:19.278 --> 21:23.081 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Stay with us.

21:23.115 --> 21:27.619 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Coming up on the "NewsHour":
Mark Shields
and David Brooks analyze the
week's news;

21:27.653 --> 21:33.925 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
basketball great Oscar Robertson
on the man
who broke his triple-double
record that has

21:33.959 --> 21:38.597 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
stood since 1962; and making the
case for
expertise.

21:38.630 --> 21:46.071 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But first: Today is Good Friday,
when Christians
around the world commemorate the
crucifixion

21:46.104 --> 21:49.374 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
of Jesus Christ, ahead of Easter
Sunday.

21:49.408 --> 21:54.946 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
One of the largest public
displays occurs
each year in Seville, Spain, but
declining

21:54.980 --> 22:00.652 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
faith among the Spanish people
is threatening
a longtime pillar of the
Catholic Church,

22:00.686 --> 22:02.888 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
its cloistered convents.

22:02.921 --> 22:04.189 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Jeffrey Brown has that story.

22:04.222 --> 22:07.693 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
It's part of our continuing
series Culture
at Risk.

22:07.726 --> 22:13.665 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: Everywhere you
turn in Seville,
tradition and history, reminders
of a rich

22:13.699 --> 22:15.701 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
religious past.

22:15.734 --> 22:23.175 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But rarely seen, Seville's
cloistered convents,
cities within cities behind high
walls, a

22:23.208 --> 22:28.513 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
piece of the fabric of the
community, yet
separate and apart, places like
the convent

22:28.547 --> 22:36.054 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
of Santa Ines, founded in 1372
by Maria Coronel,
whose body still lies in repose
in the church's

22:36.088 --> 22:37.756 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
chapel.

22:37.789 --> 22:42.728 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Prioress Maria Rebecca Cervantes
Cisneros
joined the sisterhood when she
was just 13

22:42.761 --> 22:44.463 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
years old.

22:44.496 --> 22:46.865 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
MARIA REBECCA CERVANTES
CISNEROS, Prioress
(through translator): Many
people might say

22:46.898 --> 22:50.736 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
that a person doesn't know what
she's doing
at that age, but I think that it
is a gift

22:50.769 --> 22:54.639 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
from God, and that he is free to
call for
you whenever he wishes.

22:54.673 --> 22:58.009 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And, to this day, I do not
regret having heeded
that call.

22:58.043 --> 23:02.314 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: Yet, in Spain
today, few women
heed that call.

23:02.347 --> 23:06.585 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Only about 15 percent of the
population even
attends mass.

23:06.618 --> 23:11.990 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Twenty-five years ago, there
were 41 cloistered
convents in Seville, the highest
concentration

23:12.023 --> 23:13.725 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
in Spain.

23:13.759 --> 23:19.431 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Today, just 15 active ones
remain, and at
Santa Ines, eight nuns,
practicing what's

23:19.464 --> 23:24.336 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
known as their vocation, watch
over this entire
complex.

23:24.369 --> 23:28.473 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Six of them come not from Spain,
but from
Mexico, including the prioress.

23:28.507 --> 23:33.478 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
MARIA REBECCA CERVANTES
CISNEROS: Here in
Europe, there's a very general
crisis of vocations.

23:33.512 --> 23:36.047 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Perhaps there's also a lack of
knowledge.

23:36.081 --> 23:40.185 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
Maybe we need to promote
ourselves more, because
people aren't very familiar with
us.

23:40.218 --> 23:43.555 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Many people think that the life
of a contemplative
is like a useless life.

23:43.588 --> 23:48.527 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: Convents like
Santa Ines here
in Seville are hidden treasures
from an earlier

23:48.560 --> 23:54.733 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
era, once small, but bustling
communities,
now fewer inhabitants now, and
walls that

23:54.766 --> 23:56.568 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
are decaying.

23:56.601 --> 24:01.573 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The murals lining the courtyard,
which illustrate
biblical stories and are said to
date to the

24:01.606 --> 24:04.743 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
1400s, are cracking and flaking
away.

24:04.776 --> 24:07.979 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
So, too, are many of its Spanish
tiles.

24:08.013 --> 24:10.182 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Some are held in place by
fabric.

24:10.215 --> 24:14.486 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The structural beams supporting
the entrance
to the outside world, through
which everyday

24:14.519 --> 24:21.092 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
citizens enter daily to buy
sweets through
the turnstile, are cracked, in
danger of collapsing.

24:21.126 --> 24:22.761 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Weeds grow out of every nook.

24:22.794 --> 24:25.297 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
PABLO LONGORIA, World Monuments
Fund: This
is one of the two, three
convents that is

24:25.330 --> 24:27.132 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
in worst shape.

24:27.165 --> 24:30.969 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: Pablo Longoria
directs projects
in Spain for the world monuments
fund, which

24:31.002 --> 24:36.374 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
last year added Seville's
convents to its
endangered heritage watch list.

24:36.408 --> 24:40.378 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
With his help, we were given
rare access during
the season of Lent.

24:40.412 --> 24:44.282 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Even still, many of the nuns
preferred to
remain away from our cameras.

24:44.316 --> 24:49.254 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
PABLO LONGORIA: Convents are
very old buildings
that were usually kept by the
donation of

24:49.287 --> 24:57.529 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
citizens, religious people that
would give
the convents money and products,
and by the

24:57.562 --> 24:58.763 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
nuns.

24:58.797 --> 25:01.166 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
So, 50 years ago, you would have
80 nuns in
this convent.

25:01.199 --> 25:02.467 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
Now you have eight left.

25:02.501 --> 25:03.869 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: With much less
support.

25:03.902 --> 25:07.405 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
PABLO LONGORIA: With much less
support and
with many more years.

25:07.439 --> 25:10.275 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
The average age must be 75 to 80
years.

25:10.308 --> 25:16.281 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: While Santa Ines
has imported
its nuns from Mexico, at Santa
Paula, another

25:16.314 --> 25:21.686 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
convent less than a mile away,
most of the
20 nuns are from India.

25:21.720 --> 25:27.926 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Santa Paula was established in
1473 by the
Order of Saint Jerome and,
thanks to the largess

25:27.959 --> 25:31.596 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
of the noble family of a former
prioress,
is in better shape.

25:31.630 --> 25:33.098 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: Which is your
favorite?

25:33.131 --> 25:34.099 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
WOMAN: This.

25:34.132 --> 25:35.901 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
JEFFREY BROWN: This one?

25:35.934 --> 25:39.671 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The nuns here sell their sweets
from a shop,
and even have a small museum
often open to

25:39.704 --> 25:41.406 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
the public.

25:41.439 --> 25:45.277 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But with only about a third of
its former
population, the problem of
maintaining this

25:45.310 --> 25:48.947 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
huge place remains.

25:48.980 --> 25:55.287 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
This massive church portal,
designed by Italian
sculptor Nicola Pisano and
dating to 1504,

25:55.320 --> 26:01.826 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
combines Gothic, Moorish and
Renaissance styles,
but it's been slowly destroyed
by water damage,

26:01.860 --> 26:04.396 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
spiders nests, an overall lack
of care.

26:04.429 --> 26:07.365 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
MARTA VILLANUEVA, Architect
(through translator):
It's more dark here.

26:07.399 --> 26:09.334 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
That's because of the water.

26:09.367 --> 26:12.804 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: Marta Villanueva
has been coming
here since she was a little
girl, and followed

26:12.837 --> 26:16.575 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
her father into the field of
architectural
restoration.

26:16.608 --> 26:22.147 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
She's now working on a two-year
project to
restore this portal, funded by a
$200,000

26:22.180 --> 26:25.250 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
grant from the U.S.-based
Annenberg Foundation.

26:25.283 --> 26:31.623 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MARTA VILLANUEVA (through
translator): This
facade is absolutely one of a
kind.

26:31.656 --> 26:34.593 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
There are no others like it in
all of Spain.

26:34.626 --> 26:40.198 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The most unique aspect is the
capacity it
has to unite different currents,
both aesthetically

26:40.231 --> 26:41.566 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
and in thought.

26:41.600 --> 26:44.803 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
It's a synthesis of the culture
that was enriching
all of Seville.

26:44.836 --> 26:49.674 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: But, she says,
the needs of
this convent and others far
outstrip the means

26:49.708 --> 26:51.876 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
of the nuns' orders, which own
them.

26:51.910 --> 26:56.348 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MARTA VILLANUEVA (through
translator): This
type of monument needs continual
maintenance,

26:56.381 --> 26:58.917 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
and that requires means to see
them through.

26:58.950 --> 27:00.685 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
The resources aren't always
there.

27:00.719 --> 27:04.489 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
JEFFREY BROWN: The World
Monuments Fund is
attempting to bring stakeholders
together

27:04.522 --> 27:09.628 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
in Seville, the religious
orders, the surrounding
communities and the regional
government, to

27:09.661 --> 27:12.797 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
catalogue the damage and
prioritize the greatest
needs.

27:12.831 --> 27:19.137 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
PABLO LONGORIA: The best case
scenario is,
we find, through careful study
of the building,

27:19.170 --> 27:26.211 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
a way to make it sustainable
through time,
a way in which the nuns can
stay, they can

27:26.244 --> 27:28.013 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
keep their traditions.

27:28.046 --> 27:32.417 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: Many convents
have been lost
already, abandoned or converted
into offices

27:32.450 --> 27:35.620 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
for the municipal government,
museums or event
spaces.

27:35.654 --> 27:39.524 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JAVIER RODRIGUEZ BARBERAN,
University of Seville:
You feel here like if you work
in a part of

27:39.557 --> 27:41.359 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
the convent.

27:41.393 --> 27:44.729 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: Javier Rodriguez
Barberan is
a professor of art history at
the University

27:44.763 --> 27:48.633 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
of Seville and, like many here,
grew up around
the convents.

27:48.667 --> 27:52.303 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JAVIER RODRIGUEZ BARBERAN:
Imagine there are
no nuns inside the convent.

27:52.337 --> 27:57.475 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
You can see beautiful building,
you can see
beautiful works of art, but it's
no more a

27:57.509 --> 27:58.476 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
convent.

27:58.510 --> 27:59.477 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
It would be a museum.

27:59.511 --> 28:00.812 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
It would be a hotel.

28:00.845 --> 28:05.150 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
It would be a restaurant, I
don't know, but
no more a convent.

28:05.183 --> 28:08.319 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: Which would mean
the life of
the place is gone.

28:08.353 --> 28:09.454 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JAVIER RODRIGUEZ BARBERAN:
Exactly.

28:09.487 --> 28:11.322 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
Exactly.

28:11.356 --> 28:14.325 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: At Santa Ines,
Prioress Cervantes
is asking the regional
government to make

28:14.359 --> 28:18.430 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
good on a decades-old pledge to
help restore
her convent.

28:18.463 --> 28:22.934 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
She hopes they won't have to
close this sanctuary,
but is at peace in any case.

28:22.967 --> 28:25.470 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MARIA REBECCA CERVANTES CISNEROS
(through
translator): Even though we are
concerned

28:25.503 --> 28:30.275 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
about the shortage of vocations
and such,
I think you simply forget the
present, leave

28:30.308 --> 28:34.679 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
it aside and give your life and
devotion to
the vocation we have received as
a gift, and

28:34.713 --> 28:36.214 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
the rest is up to God.

28:36.247 --> 28:45.824 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: For the "PBS
NewsHour," I'm
Jeffrey Brown in Seville, Spain.

28:45.857 --> 28:57.235 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Now we turn to
politics, starting
with the backlash some GOP
