30:31.362 --> 30:32.897 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
But I'm not going to do it every
other day.

30:32.931 --> 30:34.666 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
It's when it's something
significant.

30:34.699 --> 30:39.804 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Attendees at that
event had
to show an I.D., and limit signs
to notebook

30:39.838 --> 30:41.272 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
size.

30:41.306 --> 30:45.643 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Other Republicans have opted
against holding
mass voter events at all.

30:45.677 --> 30:50.849 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Instead, some are conducting
tele-town halls
over the phone and social media.

30:50.882 --> 30:58.556 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
A big question is, will the
anger translate
beyond town halls?

30:58.590 --> 31:05.496 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
This week in Kansas, in a
rock-solid Republican
district, the GOP only narrowly
won a special

31:05.530 --> 31:11.769 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
election for the House seat
vacated by Mike
Pompeo, who's now director of
the CIA.

31:11.803 --> 31:18.142 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
There's another closely watched
special House
election next Tuesday in Georgia
to replace

31:18.176 --> 31:23.314 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Tom Price, the new secretary of
health and
human services.

31:23.348 --> 31:26.484 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And with that, we turn to the
analysis of
Shields and Brooks.

31:26.517 --> 31:30.822 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
That's syndicated columnist Mark
Shields and
New York Times columnist David
Brooks.

31:30.855 --> 31:32.557 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Welcome,
gentlemen.

31:32.590 --> 31:37.662 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
So, David, what do you make of
all this hostility
at some of the town halls?

31:37.695 --> 31:39.530 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
DAVID BROOKS: Yes, I think there
are two issues
here.

31:39.564 --> 31:40.965 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
One is the hostility of the town
hall.

31:40.999 --> 31:42.800 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
I'm not sure what to make of
that.

31:42.834 --> 31:48.539 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
I think it means that
progressives are as
enraged as the Tea Party people
were of several

31:48.573 --> 31:50.275 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
years ago.

31:50.308 --> 31:53.044 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The larger issue is the shift in
the polls
in that Kansas race and some of
the other

31:53.077 --> 31:55.780 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
races and the shift that we see
in the polls
generally.

31:55.813 --> 32:00.818 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And that's less -- that's not
only the fact
progressives are more energized,
but it's

32:00.852 --> 32:04.789 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
also the drifting away of
Republicans from
the Trump administration.

32:04.822 --> 32:07.792 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And it's not happening on a
state level, so
this is Trump-related.

32:07.825 --> 32:12.030 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And so, if I were a House member
with -- maybe
if I had won my last seat, and I
am Republican,

32:12.063 --> 32:16.701 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
by 10 or 15 points, I think I
would be more
nervous than ever before in my
career.

32:16.734 --> 32:19.637 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: What do you
attribute all this
to?

32:19.671 --> 32:24.642 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MARK SHIELDS: Well, first of
all, Judy, the
Joe Wilson segment was
particularly appropriate,

32:24.676 --> 32:26.244 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
South Carolina.

32:26.277 --> 32:32.083 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
It was September 2009 where Joe
Wilson, I
think, changed American
politics.

32:32.116 --> 32:35.620 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
He was a member of the House of
Representatives
then, as he is now.

32:35.653 --> 32:40.258 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
President Barack Obama was
addressing the
Congress on Medicare, joint
session, and the

32:40.291 --> 32:45.396 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
president said illegal
undocumented immigrants
wouldn't be covered under the
health care

32:45.430 --> 32:47.165 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
plan.

32:47.198 --> 32:53.604 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
And Joe Wilson broke all
customs, traditions
and stood up and said, "You lie,
you lie,"

32:53.638 --> 32:57.075 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
and he was reprimanded
officially by the House
of Representatives.

32:57.108 --> 32:58.076 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
He had to apologize.

32:58.109 --> 32:59.777 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
He apologized personally.

32:59.811 --> 33:03.147 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
He raised $1.5 million the next
week.

33:03.181 --> 33:09.420 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And that's when it -- learned
that there wasn't
a consequence to such behavior.

33:09.454 --> 33:15.059 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And it sort of, I think, really
raised to
a different level the
polarization and the

33:15.093 --> 33:19.263 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
personalization of our politics,
that anything
goes as long as you raise money.

33:19.297 --> 33:20.865 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: It was kind of a
turning point.

33:20.898 --> 33:22.667 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
MARK SHIELDS: I really feel that
way.

33:22.700 --> 33:25.536 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
So, I agree with David.

33:25.570 --> 33:30.975 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I think there is energy, there's
no question,
and passion, just as there was
then against

33:31.009 --> 33:34.345 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
President Obama in 2009, 2010.

33:34.379 --> 33:40.651 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
There isn't any trace of any
racial component
to the opposition to President
Trump, but

33:40.685 --> 33:42.286 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
there is passion.

33:42.320 --> 33:44.122 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
And I think that's what you see.

33:44.155 --> 33:49.193 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
What I would be worried about,
Democrats should
be, that this looks
orchestrated, that it

33:49.227 --> 33:53.765 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
looks planned, that the
Democratic National
Committee sent out a message
saying, get in

33:53.798 --> 34:00.038 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Jeff Flake's grill, so that it's
not just
a question of spontaneity, of
people expressing

34:00.071 --> 34:06.978 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
their own opposition or
criticism about policies,
but, instead, sort of
organizing.

34:07.011 --> 34:10.381 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
If it starts to ring of an
organized effort,
I think it hurts.

34:10.415 --> 34:16.654 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
As far as the special House
elections, they're
always aberrational, but if the
Democrats

34:16.687 --> 34:21.559 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
are going to win the House in
2018, they have
to win districts like the one in
Georgia,

34:21.592 --> 34:22.560 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
which...

34:22.593 --> 34:24.228 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: The one that is
up next Tuesday.

34:24.262 --> 34:26.998 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MARK SHIELDS: ... Mitt Romney
won by 20 points
and Donald Trump only won by
two.

34:27.031 --> 34:31.836 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
It's twice as college-educated a
population,
electorate as the reset of the
state.

34:31.869 --> 34:34.305 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And this is the kind of place
they have to
break through.

34:34.338 --> 34:39.143 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: What determines,
David, whether
Democrats stay energized or not?

34:39.177 --> 34:43.714 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
DAVID BROOKS: Well, we have
learned that hatred
is the organizing -- the great
organizing

34:43.748 --> 34:45.616 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
principle in politics.

34:45.650 --> 34:50.354 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And, of course, they have done
so poorly in
the midterms because their
output, their turnout

34:50.388 --> 34:53.558 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
tends to be low in those races.

34:53.591 --> 34:58.529 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
You know, to me, it's very
hazardous to linearly
project out.

34:58.563 --> 35:03.067 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
We have seen in the last week
the Trump administration
shift in a radical way.

35:03.101 --> 35:07.572 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And so something really bad
could happen,
something really good could
happen, but the

35:07.605 --> 35:11.375 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
odds that the future a year from
now will
look like the present, those
strike me as

35:11.409 --> 35:12.844 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
infinitesimally low.

35:12.877 --> 35:16.280 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
We're in a position there is
just wide variance
on what could happen.

35:16.314 --> 35:21.018 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And so I'm not sure it makes
much sense to
think, what is 2018 going to
look like, because

35:21.052 --> 35:24.589 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
there are probably -- as many
days as there
are between now and then, that's
how many

35:24.622 --> 35:26.357 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
changes of directions we're
probably going
to see.

35:26.390 --> 35:31.929 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MARK SHIELDS: One quick measure
of prospects
is the ability to translate that
enthusiasm

35:31.963 --> 35:33.731 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
into contributions.

35:33.764 --> 35:39.137 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And the Democratic candidate in
Georgia, Jon
Ossoff, who is really untried,
untested, I

35:39.170 --> 35:44.609 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
mean, a young man, 30 years old,
with a very
thin resume, has raised over
$8.5 million.

35:44.642 --> 35:47.378 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Much of it from
out of state.

35:47.411 --> 35:49.914 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
MARK SHIELDS: Most of it
overwhelmingly from
out of state.

35:49.947 --> 35:55.153 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
When the Democrats did last
capture the House
from the Republicans in 2006,
one of the reasons

35:55.186 --> 36:00.958 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
they did is that the Democrats,
under Rahm
Emanuel's leadership, now the
mayor of Chicago,

36:00.992 --> 36:07.498 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
devoted incredible effort to
recruiting candidates
who fit with the districts in
which they ran.

36:07.532 --> 36:12.170 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
That's when they ran Blue Dog
Democrats, conservative
to moderate Democrats in
conservative to moderate

36:12.203 --> 36:13.938 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
areas.

36:13.971 --> 36:16.908 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Since then, they have kind of
turned over
the nominating process to
national liberal

36:16.941 --> 36:19.710 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
groups and whomever they
support.

36:19.744 --> 36:22.713 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And I think that's been a
mistake and I think
they have paid for it at the
polls.

36:22.747 --> 36:25.650 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
DAVID BROOKS: If I could make
one quick comment
about the town halls, I probably
wouldn't

36:25.683 --> 36:26.651 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
go to them.

36:26.684 --> 36:28.452 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
Like, I love political
discussion.

36:28.486 --> 36:32.890 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But having people shout at each
other, even
if you agree, it's just -- I
think it's bad

36:32.924 --> 36:34.292 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
in general.

36:34.325 --> 36:35.960 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Whether you agree with them or
not, it's just
not a conversation.

36:35.993 --> 36:38.396 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
It's just umbrage and it's a
little bit theatrical.

36:38.429 --> 36:40.531 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: But they used to
be very quiet,
didn't they?

36:40.565 --> 36:42.333 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
This is a big change.

36:42.366 --> 36:45.136 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But, David, you mentioned a
minute ago something
that I do want to ask you both
about.

36:45.169 --> 36:50.808 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And that is what appears to be a
change in
position by the president on a
number of things,

36:50.841 --> 36:56.447 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
around trade, around NAFTA, that
he's going
to declare China a currency
manipulator on

36:56.480 --> 36:59.116 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
day one, that he's going to get
health care
passed.

36:59.150 --> 37:02.386 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And that's a different issue,
that you have
to have Congress go along.

37:02.420 --> 37:03.688 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
DAVID BROOKS: Janet Yellen at
the...

37:03.721 --> 37:05.690 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Janet Yellen, the
chairman
of the Federal Reserve.

37:05.723 --> 37:06.691 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
DAVID BROOKS: Right.

37:06.724 --> 37:07.992 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: What's going on
here?

37:08.025 --> 37:10.361 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Are these genuine changes of
opinion?

37:10.394 --> 37:11.596 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
What -- how do you see it?

37:11.629 --> 37:12.597 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
DAVID BROOKS: Certainly struck
by it.

37:12.630 --> 37:14.498 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
There are a lot of data points
all of a sudden.

37:14.532 --> 37:18.903 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And most people, if they --
especially if
you're an academic or an writer,
if you spend

37:18.936 --> 37:23.474 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
many months arguing that China's
a manipulator,
a currency manipulator, you
don't just then

37:23.507 --> 37:24.475 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
turn on a dime.

37:24.508 --> 37:26.777 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
But Donald Trump is different.

37:26.811 --> 37:28.112 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
He's a marketing guy.

37:28.145 --> 37:30.381 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
He's a business guy, whatever is
working for
him at the moment.

37:30.414 --> 37:35.086 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And it seems, from this many
data points,
he's making the conclusion that
the populism

37:35.119 --> 37:38.689 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
and the Bannon-ism is not
working, and he's
going to go to something else.

37:38.723 --> 37:42.126 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Now, what exactly that else
thing is, we don't
really know.

37:42.159 --> 37:43.961 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
It could be sort of a
corporatism.

37:43.995 --> 37:48.366 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
It could be, let me trust my
business guys,
let's go to the CEOs, and let's
-- those guys,

37:48.399 --> 37:50.201 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
I can trust.

37:50.234 --> 37:55.139 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
There seems to be some
instinctual sense that
he's shifting teams of who he
wants to be

37:55.172 --> 37:56.807 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
his key advisers.

37:56.841 --> 38:00.478 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And with Trump, because he knows
so little,
it's not him personal initiating
policy.

38:00.511 --> 38:02.780 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The crucial question is, who is
he listening
to?

38:02.813 --> 38:07.184 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And there's a clear shift, at
least in one
week, that there has been a
radical shift

38:07.218 --> 38:09.020 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
in his advisee team.

38:09.053 --> 38:16.560 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: But it is a
remarkable number
of issues that the president
appears, Mark,

38:16.594 --> 38:20.131 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
to be taking the opposite stand
from what
he said during the campaign.

38:20.164 --> 38:22.199 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
MARK SHIELDS: No, you're right,
Judy.

38:22.233 --> 38:27.438 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Even during the campaign, when
he said things
that were inconsistent or
occasionally contradictory,

38:27.471 --> 38:33.411 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
the defense, the rebuttal of
this on the part
of his supporters was, hey, he
may not always

38:33.444 --> 38:38.783 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
be -- but he says what he means,
and he means
what he says, and the guy just
doesn't say

38:38.816 --> 38:42.486 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
it all of the time with polish,
but he says
it with conviction.

38:42.520 --> 38:47.558 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Well, his convictions turned out
to have the
shelf life of a used kleenex.

38:47.591 --> 38:49.860 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
They just disappear.

38:49.894 --> 38:56.667 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
So, you know, now he's moved
toward orthodoxy,
sort of a Republican orthodoxy,
business -- pro-business

38:56.701 --> 39:02.840 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
orthodoxy, international
responsibility, America
is the -- if not the policeman
of the world,

39:02.873 --> 39:06.911 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
then certainly a projector of
force and influence
in maintaining security around
the world.

39:06.944 --> 39:10.281 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: I mean, just in
the last week,
the bomb that was dropped in
Afghanistan,

39:10.314 --> 39:11.682 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
the strike in Syria, right.

39:11.716 --> 39:13.617 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
MARK SHIELDS: The bomb in
Afghanistan.

39:13.651 --> 39:19.690 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But in both Afghanistan and
Syria, there wasn't
any consequence of -- real
likely consequence

39:19.724 --> 39:23.728 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
of any national retaliation to
the United
States.

39:23.761 --> 39:25.663 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
They were enormous acts.

39:25.696 --> 39:27.965 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
I mean, they got the world's
attention.

39:27.998 --> 39:29.834 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
North Korea is different.

39:29.867 --> 39:35.473 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And tough talk in North Korea is
not going
to stop Kim Jong-un from -- I
don't think,

39:35.506 --> 39:37.308 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
from a nuclear test.

